# ACCESS VisionCheck тАФ Self-Annealing Notes (Agent)

Read this before changing backend models, routes, or Flutter navigation. These rules exist because we already hit these bugs once.

## 1. Never тАЬtemporarilyтАЭ unregister API routes

**Mistake:** Refactored SQLAlchemy models and left `app/api/routes/__init__.py` with only `auth`, `health`, `users`, `rankings`. Flutter still called `/api/admin/stats` тЖТ **404** тЖТ dashboard showed тАЬRequest failed (404)тАЭ and fake demo numbers.

**Rule:** If you change models/CRUD, you must either:
- Keep every route the Flutter app calls **registered** in `api_router`, or
- Update Flutter (`lib/shared/api/*.dart`) in the **same change**, or
- Stub the endpoint with a clear `501` and update the UI тАФ never silent 404.

**Before finishing backend work, run this checklist:**
1. Open `lib/shared/api/admin_api_service.dart` and `auth_service.dart` тАФ list every path.
2. Open `access_backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py` тАФ confirm each path has a router included.
3. Restart server and hit `GET /api/health` plus one authenticated admin route.
4. Tell the user to restart `python manage.py runserver` after route changes.

## 2. Flutter тЖФ FastAPI route contract (prefix `/api`)

| Flutter call | Must exist on backend |
|--------------|----------------------|
| `POST /auth/login` | `auth.router` |
| `POST /auth/register` | `auth.router` |
| `GET /admin/stats` | `admin.router` тЖТ `/admin/stats` |
| `GET /admin/service-requests` | `admin.router` |
| `PATCH /service-requests/{id}` | `documentation_requests.router` |
| `GET /users` | `users.router` |
| `PATCH /users/{id}/status` | `users.router` |
| `GET /rankings` | `rankings.router` |
| `GET /events` | тЪая╕П not registered yet тАФ add before using Events UI |
| `GET /admin/evaluations` | тЪая╕П not registered yet |
| `GET /feedback` | тЪая╕П not registered yet |

When adding a new screen that calls the API, add the row to this table and implement the route same PR.

## 3. Schema migration тЙа delete old behavior

**Mistake:** New tables (`users.fullname`, `roles`, `documentation_requests`) but CRUD still used `password_hash`, `UserRole` enum, `user_id` тЖТ login broke or 500тАЩd.

**Rule:** After changing `app/models/*`:
- Update `app/crud/*`, `app/api/routes/*`, `app/schemas/*` in the same pass.
- Map legacy Flutter field names in API responses when needed (`user_id` тЖТ `id`, `name` тЖТ `fullname`, `Pending` vs `pending`).
- Run `python create_tables.py` only when schema changes; use `RECREATE_DB=true` only in dev.

## 4. Web admin white screen after login

**Mistake:** `adminBuilder: (_) => const SizedBox.shrink()` in `lib/mobile_app/controllers/app.dart` тЖТ admin login succeeded but UI was empty.

**Rule:** On `kIsWeb`, admin must use `WebAdminShell`. Root `lib/main.dart` should route web тЖТ `web_admin/main_web.dart`.

## 5. Network / CORS / API host

- Flutter API base: `lib/shared/constants/api_config.dart` тЖТ `API_PUBLIC_HOST` in `.env` (default `10.0.22.98`).
- Backend bind: `API_HOST=0.0.0.0`, `API_PORT=3001`.
- CORS must allow Flutter Web dev origins (`localhost:<random_port>`) тАФ see `access_backend/main.py`.
- **404 on LAN IP but 200 on 127.0.0.1** usually means an **old uvicorn process** тАФ restart backend.

