- **2026-05:** Mobile bottom-nav showed "Profile" label with the analytics icon тАФ `_navItems` had 9 entries but `_screen` only mapped 0..6, so slot 6 displayed `_navItems[6].icon` (Analytics) under the "Profile" label. Fixed by trimming `_navItems` to exactly the 7 screens in order (Home, Evaluations, Calendar, Gallery, Feedback, Rankings, Profile) and deleting the dead `_Sidebar` widget.

## 9. Design tokens тАФ do NOT regress

These tokens live in `lib/shared/themes/theme.dart` and define the entire mobile + web design system. Any UI change MUST use them; no inline hex values for these slots.

| Token | Hex | Purpose |
|----|----|----|
| `kBg` | `0xFFF8FAFC` | Page background |
| `kSurface` | `0xFFFFFFFF` | Card surface |
| `kAccent` | `0xFF2563EB` | Primary icon color тАФ ALL stat/feature card icons + active bottom-nav |
| `kIconInactive` | `0xFF94A3B8` | Inactive bottom-nav icons + label |
| `kTextPrimary` | `0xFF1E293B` | Main text |
| `kTextSecondary` | `0xFF64748B` | Secondary text |
| `kBorder` | `0xFFE2E8F0` | Card / input borders |

- Feature/stat cards: use `AccessStatCard` from `lib/mobile_app/widgets/stat_card.dart`. Never hand-roll another card body тАФ the radius/padding/shadow/icon-tile contract must stay identical across screens.
- Bottom nav: icons must all be the rounded variants (`Icons.dashboard_rounded`, `Icons.analytics_rounded`, etc.). Active = `kAccent`, inactive = `kIconInactive`. No per-item colors.
- No mixed icon colors (green/purple/orange/brown) on cards. Semantic colors (`kGreen`/`kYellow`/`kRed`) are only for status badges (e.g. "ACTIVE", "Meets standards"), not for card icons.

## 8. Mobile API base URL тАФ DO NOT regress

- `lib/shared/constants/api_config.dart`:
  - Web тЖТ `127.0.0.1` (override: `API_WEB_HOST`).
  - Android default тЖТ `10.0.2.2` (emulator alias тАФ DO NOT change to a LAN IP).
  - Physical phone тЖТ user pastes PC LAN IPv4 from the in-app "Set backend URL" dialog (`ApiConfig.runtimeBaseUrl`, persisted via SharedPreferences) OR developer passes `--dart-define=API_PUBLIC_HOST=192.168.x.x` (or full `API_BASE_URL`).
- NEVER write `localhost` / `127.0.0.1` into the Android default тАФ those resolve to the phone itself.
- `ApiConfig.runtimeBaseUrl.load()` MUST be awaited in `main_mobile.dart` and `main_web.dart` BEFORE `runApp(...)`. Otherwise the first API call uses the wrong default.
- After changing the API host, restart the app (not just hot reload) so the http client picks up the new `baseUrl`.
- Before claiming "mobile shows data": confirm the orange `MobileOfflineBanner` is NOT visible after login. Tap it тЖТ "Set backend URL" lets the phone user fix it on-device.
